attributeDefinition: Identifier for research cruise, generally including abbreviation for research vessel and voyage number
Longitudinal stations along established NES-LTER transect and MVCO. If a station does not begin with an 'L', it is an opportunistic sample collected off the longitudinal transect.
Chronological CTD rosette cast number per cruise.
Type of nest cast: oblique or vertical.
Type of net deployed: Bongo or ring.
Mesh size of the net used.
Size range (in micron) of sample size fractions, from smaller to larger.
Principal investigation (PI) or lab responsible for storing or processing the sample.
Method of preservation used on the sample.
Fraction of the sample jar used for a respective sample from each net.
Number of jars or containers used for the sample.
Comments from the paper field sheets.
Comments explaining why a sample is missing.
